Data Structures and Algorithms Lab (C)
Overview

This repository contains my implementations of Data Structures and Algorithms using the C programming language as part of my lab work. It focuses on building a strong understanding of core concepts and improving problem-solving skills.

Contents

The repository includes programs based on the following topics:

Basics of C programming
Arrays and Strings
Searching algorithms (Linear Search, Binary Search)
Sorting algorithms (Bubble Sort, Selection Sort, Insertion Sort, etc.)
Recursion
Linked Lists
Stacks and Queues
Trees and basic Graph concepts
Language Used
C
How to Run
Clone the repository:
git clone
Navigate to the folder:
cd

Compile and run any program:

gcc filename.c
./a.out

Purpose
Understand fundamental DSA concepts
Practice coding in C
Prepare for technical interviews
Improve logical thinking
Future Improvements
Add comments and explanations for each program
Include time and space complexity
Organize programs topic-wise in folders
Add more advanced DSA problems
